What's new?
***********

A list of all new features in AmIRC v2.0
========================================

   @{b}*@{ub} Invitations are now shown in an seperate @{b}Invite requester@{ub}. The
     requester can be disabled from the new 'Windows' section in the
     preferences.

   @{b}*@{ub} The @{b}Lag-O-Meter@{ub} permanently monitors and shows lag as a
     three-color bar underneath the userlist. Clicking on the
     Lag-O-Meter opens the Information window, which has a graphical
     representation of the current lag, as well as the servername,
     current lag, last two lag probes and the average lag.

   @{b}*@{ub} Frequently used channels can be stored in a @{b}Favorite Channels@{ub}
     window from where you can join them by doubleclicking on them.

   @{b}*@{ub} The new @{b}Tray window@{ub} contains a button for every AmIRC window.
     Windows can be closed individually by clicking on their 'Hide'
     gadget. The Tray window shows number of messages in a window and
     indicates new messages after iconification. (Requires MUI v3.8+)

   @{b}*@{ub} Dialog windows have a @{b}Rename@{ub} button to change the nick for the
     window. Useful when someone re-enters IRC with a different nick.

   @{b}*@{ub} Dialog and Channel windows have an @{b}[L]@{ub} button to enable logging of
     that windowto a file.

   @{b}*@{ub} AmIRC now uses @{b}NList.mcc@{ub} for it's listviews if found.

   @{b}*@{ub} DCC windows now have a @{b}Cleanup@{ub} button to delete all finished or
     aborted transfers at once.

   @{b}*@{ub} The @{b}/BACK@{ub} command resets the Away state no matter what it is.

   @{b}*@{ub} DCC Receive window has a @{b}Replace@{ub} button to overwrite existing
     files.

   @{b}*@{ub} DCC Reveive window has a @{b}MIMEPrefs@{ub} button to call up the MIMEPrefs
     program.

   @{b}*@{ub} The @{b}Auto accept DCC send?@{ub} menu item allows to start incoming DCC
     send requests without the need for confirmation.

   @{b}*@{ub} AmIRC now uses @{b}MIMEPrefs@{ub} for for viewing files.

   @{b}*@{ub} AmIRC now has a @{b}Plugin API@{ub}, expect many seperately developed
     extension modules.

   @{b}*@{ub} The Serverlist is now divided into @{b}Server Groups@{ub} to allow better
     organization of different servers of a network.

   @{b}*@{ub} The Prefs menu has a new @{b}Windows@{ub} section where can be determined
     which windows will open on startup.


@EndNode

